==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Radiancy
<hw>Ra"di*an*cy</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"d⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧n*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of being radiant; brilliancy; effulgence;
vivid brightness; <as>as, the <ex>radiance</ex> of the
sun</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Girt with omnipotence, with <qex>radiance</qex> crowned.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>radiancy</qex> of glory,⟦br⟧
What light beyond compare !</q> <rj><qau>Neale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Luster; brilliancy; splendor; glare;
glitter.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Radiant</ent>⟦br⟧
